---
title: Rustic Farro & Pork Sausage Soup with Parmesan
description: Few things are more satisfying than a pot of hearty, soul-warming soup (aka the culinary equivalent of a cozy blanket). This one is chock full of goodness—that is to say crumbled pork sausage, aromatic veggies, Tuscan herbs and spices, and chewy farro. Of course, no soup would be complete without a cheesy topping—here, we sprinkle over savory Parmesan for melt-factor. Soup’s on!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/rustic-farro-pork-sausage-soup-8a021672.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/rustic-farro-pork-sausage-soup-5f8dfae348b2722f4849b830-6e5447b5.pdf
time required: 45 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 740 kcal
  fat: 36 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 71 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1550 mg
cuisine: Italian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/rustic-farro-and-pork-sausage-soup-5f8dfae348b2722f4849b830
---

Wash and dry all produce. Trim, peel, and cut @carrot{3%ounce}(peeled and diced) into a small dice. Halve, peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Remove @Italian pork sausage{9%ounce} from casing; discard casing.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pot over medium-high heat. Add sausage and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{4-6%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step). Meanwhile, dice @roma tomato{1}(diced). Pick @parsley{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves.

Add another drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} to #pot with sausage; stir in carrot, onion, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are just softened and sausage is cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir tomato, half the chopped parsley, half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon} (use the rest as you like), and @farro{½%cup} into #pot with sausage mixture. (Use 1 cup farro for 4 servings.) Cook, stirring, ~{1%minute}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2} and 3½ cups warm water (6 cups for 4), scraping up any browned bits from bottom of #pot. Cover, bring to a boil, then immediately reduce heat to low. Simmer, covered, until farro is tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Stir half the @parmesan cheese{¼%cup}(grated) (save the rest for serving) into soup. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Top with remaining Parmesan and chopped parsley and serve.